properties.name: 10 km
properties.descriptio: An excellent alternative when the road to the top is still wet and gated.

properties.name: 5 km
properties.descriptio: One of the more classic sections of DH trail in Golden.

properties.name: 5 km Alt
properties.descriptio: Alternative Line

properties.name: 5 km Alt
properties.descriptio: A less steep connector

properties.name: 6 km
properties.descriptio: A connector trail with some steep sections.

properties.name: Arrowhead
properties.descriptio: Arrowhead flows along a ridge and best ridden north to south. Popular with great views and a ‘must ride’.

properties.name: B12
properties.descriptio: Steep in a fun old school way.  Some exposure and avoid when wet.

properties.name: Barking Dog
properties.descriptio: A sweet singletrack along Cedar 2 Lake which connects Arrowhead to Cedar Camp and named after a mutt called Max.

properties.name: Better Than Boston
properties.descriptio: This fast flowing singletrack connects Arrowhead to North Star. The reference to Boston has nothing to do with hockey and everything to do with running.

properties.name: Bris
properties.descriptio: Steep technical downhill sections.

properties.name: Canyon Creek
properties.descriptio: The Golden classic and begins with a singletrack which eventually widens to an old wagon road, all along the rim of a 200 m canyon. Use the 200 m reroute GCC built to help protect some sensitive goat habitat and expect pedestrian traffic. Avoid riding up

properties.name: Canyon Creek
properties.descriptio: The Golden classic and begins with a singletrack which eventually widens to an old wagon road, all along the rim of a 200 m canyon. Use the 200 m reroute GCC built to help protect some sensitive goat habitat and expect pedestrian traffic. Avoid riding up

properties.name: Cedar Camp
properties.descriptio: A rolling trail along both Cedar 1 and Cedar 2 lakes, Cedar Camp provides a link to North Star.

properties.name: Cedar Lake Rd
properties.descriptio: Road

properties.name: Cedar Snag
properties.descriptio: Beautiful singletrack along Cedar 3 and 4 lakes. North end is rooty but can be avoided via a short connector.

properties.name: Chute the Duck
properties.descriptio: A grunt of a climb or a fun, flowy downhill exit.

properties.name: Cliff Side
properties.descriptio: Rides both directions. Steep, technical and aesthetic climbing both ways are rewarded by spectacular views of the Columbia Valley wetlands.

properties.name: Connector
properties.descriptio: Connector

properties.name: Damn Bypass
properties.descriptio: A new trail constructed to allow a more direct access from the Gudjonson trailhead to the upper end of the Canyon Creek trail.

properties.name: Dead Dog
properties.descriptio: The classic Psychosis drop-in.  Steep is an understatement.

properties.name: Devil's Slide
properties.descriptio: Short, but fast fun.  Drops from the tower to Klahowya at a 10% grade.  Ride only in downhill direction.

properties.name: Elk Road
properties.descriptio: Road

properties.name: Erich's
properties.descriptio: Another alternative when you can't get to the top.  Great features.

properties.name: Gold Rush
properties.descriptio: The south end of this trail slowly gains elevation until it meets the BC Hydro right of way and from there the trail drops steeply to Elk road. The trail is closed to uphill traffic from Elk road to the right of way but watch for traffic emerging from th

properties.name: Huff & Puff
properties.descriptio: Rides both ways, more commonly ridden downhill north to Quenton’s which connects to Roller Coaster or Chute the Duck as an exit route to town.

properties.name: Jeep Road
properties.descriptio: Access to the top for OHVs.

properties.name: Kamikaze
properties.descriptio: A classic steep finish to B12.  Straight down to the river.

properties.name: Kissime Lookout
properties.descriptio: Parallels the Ptarmigan Trot trail along a ridge. There is no lookout.

properties.name: Kobe's
properties.descriptio: Rides well in both directions, but the climb from the north is technical. Negotiates some attractive rock bluffs. This is a good approach for the upper level trails such as Rock About.

properties.name: LSD Access Road
properties.descriptio: Get to LSD

properties.name: Magic Dragon
properties.descriptio: Rides well in both directions. Includes intermediate to advanced wood/rock stunts and jump options at the north end.

properties.name: Moonraker
properties.descriptio: Best ridden from north to south with a climb followed by a fun roller coaster ride to the lower Canyon Creek lookout.

properties.name: Moonshine
properties.descriptio: Another section of the great Psychosis trail.

properties.name: North Star
properties.descriptio: Similar to Cedar Snag in terrain and aspect but with some steeper climbs.

properties.name: Old Age/Treachery
properties.descriptio: Accessed from the south end of CBT Mainline, this trail is best ridden if you turn right at the midway junction. Expect short technical sections above Cedar creek. The trail exits onto Alpine Meadows trail opposite the Gold Rush trail which is the recomm

properties.name: Quinton's
properties.descriptio: Rides both ways, but more common from the south to the north. It is a classic single track with clear sight lines that is a great place to go for an after work quickie.

properties.name: Reflection Lake
properties.descriptio: The main Mtn Shadows entrance  trail, a nice climb with a few steeper cruxes. For a good introduction to the Shadows, try the original combo of Reflection Lake to Quenton’s to Roller Coaster. Reflection Lake trail is also the easiest way down.

properties.name: Road
properties.descriptio: Road

properties.name: Road
properties.descriptio: Road

properties.name: Rock About
properties.descriptio: Get your rocks off on this epic piece of bench-cut trail and switchbacks. This trail climbs to the highest elevation in the Shadows system. The rocky sections at the north end are challenging in both directions.

properties.name: Selkirk Slacker
properties.descriptio: A fun access and exit traverse from the Selkirk Heights neighborhood.

properties.name: Skid Marks
properties.descriptio: Another section linking up the great Psychosis trail.

properties.name: Sternwheeler
properties.descriptio: Built in 2013 to connect the new Gudjonson trailhead to the Canyon Creek and 2% trails.

properties.name: Summit
properties.descriptio: A side hill trail representing a more modest way off Mount 7.

properties.name: Summit Connector
properties.descriptio: Connector to Summit

properties.name: Tail Gate Alt
properties.descriptio: Keep left for an alternative line to the bottom.

properties.name: Tail Gate/Snake Hill
properties.descriptio: Awesome.  Fast banked corners in a gulley with a big jump at the end.

properties.name: Take it Easy
properties.descriptio: This trail works its way along the west bank of the Columbia River (watch for cliffs between you and the Columbia!) with little net elevation gain but lots of small ups and downs. Can be ridden as an out and back or as an exit for the Gold Rush trail. A

properties.name: Tallis Road
properties.descriptio: Road

properties.name: The Mighty Quinn
properties.descriptio: An instant hit when completed in 2013, this machine built, roller coaster of a trail is one way (no uphill traffic) and features lots of berms and rollers. Enjoy!

properties.name: Tomorrow We Ride
properties.descriptio: A short alternate route at the south end of Tonight Tequila.

properties.name: Tonight Tequila
properties.descriptio: The first trail built in our 2010 expansion, this fast, largely flat singletrack passes through a great mix of terrain. The north end features a series of eight switchbacks as it ascends to Arrowhead.

properties.name: Tower Road
properties.descriptio: Quicker than Bear Claw, but you’re not here to ride roads.

properties.name: Trial & Error
properties.descriptio: Rides both ways. High speed reclaimed roads on the upper section and some technical rock bluffs on the lower section.

properties.name: True Value/3 km
properties.descriptio: Enjoyable fast flowy downhill with a few tough spots.

properties.name: Wapiti Ridge
properties.descriptio: When combined with Private Lands this trail allows access to the Moonrakers from the bottom of the Canyon Creek trail.

properties.name: Woodlot Ride
properties.descriptio: An access option.

properties.name: Ptarmagin Trot
properties.descriptio: The west part of this trail around Sander Lake is a relatively easy loop and can be done by novice riders.  The east side contains numerous rocks and roots.

properties.name: Roller Coaster
properties.descriptio: Downhill only, a series of steep berms down a gully.

properties.name: Klahowya
properties.descriptio: The sister trail to Bear Claw, collecting riders from other trails and delivering them to Sander Lake. With Ptarmigan Trot this is the quickest way to get from Sander Lake to a view point at Canyon Creek.

properties.name: Bear Claw
properties.descriptio: With access points at Sander Lake, Tower road and the lower Canyon Creek lookout, Bear Claw serves as a singletrack access to trails at the south end of the Moonrakers.

properties.name: Alpine Meadows
properties.descriptio: This double track, former skid road has plenty of room for novice riders.  However it’s steep sections will have you breathing hard.

properties.name: Windago Chute
properties.descriptio: A steep connector skidder trail between Klahowya and Bear Claw

properties.name: CBT Mainline
properties.descriptio: Built in 2010 to link the Moonraker network to Golden, the popularity of this trail led to the subsequent development of the Mainline network. The trail traverses three benches providing everything from challenging switchbacks to flowing singletrack. Wat

properties.name: Alpine Meadows
properties.descriptio: This double track, former skid road has plenty of room for novice riders.  However it’s steep sections will have you breathing hard.
